    StellarOSCVocabulary

    public final class StellarOSCVocabulary.CommandMessages
extends java.lang.Object
    CommandMessages are sent from OSC client to StellarCommand Direct where our message will be filtered by StellarCommand

      • STELLAR_TIME

        public static final java.lang.String STELLAR_TIME
        Set the time on stellarium. This can be set with either a single string with full ISO time or as OSC arguments for the date and time
        If the first OSC agrgument is a string, the code will attempt to decode as ISO string
        ISO time as String OR Year as Integer
        Month as Integer
        Day of month as Integer
        Hour as Integer in 24 Hour time
        Minutes as integer
        Seconds as a float
        Optional Time zone as Z or +/-HHH:mm as a String. EG "Z" or "+10:00". If no argument, the local time of location will be used
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
